   "common": [
      {
         "text": "### Sui Dynasty (隋代)\n\nWhen we talk about dynasties, whether in the West or the East, we generally associate them with a family ruling a region for generations. This fact leads us to an initial reflection.",
         "source": null,
         "date_time": null,
         "isTable": false,
         "imgdesc": "",
         "format": "markdown",
         "PostMention": ""
      },
      {
         "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: At least...</b><br /><br />The Sui Dynasty (隋代) had only three rulers during its existence (<htdate0>-<htdate1>), but in that short span of time, they accomplished a great deal.<br /><br />To define a dynasty, what is more important: the number of rulers or the achievements of those people?</div></div></center></p>",
         "source": null,
         "date_time": [
               {
                  "type": "gregory",
                  "year": "581",
                  "month": "",
                  "day": ""
               },
               {
                  "type": "gregory",
                  "year": "618",
                  "month": "",
                  "day": ""
               }
         ],
         "isTable": false,
         "imgdesc": "",
         "format": "html",
         "PostMention": ""
      },
      {
         "text": "#### Together we are strong\n\nOne of the great achievements of the Sui Dynasty (隋代) was the unification of China after three centuries, a fact that allowed the development of art and culture, as well as administrative reforms (<htcite0>; <htcite1>; <htcite2>).\n\nThe period of unification was also marked by another important event in East Asia that, in addition to China (Zhongguo 中國), also occurred in Japan (Nihon koku 日本国): the establishment of Buddhism in these regions (<htcite3>; <htcite4>).\n\nThe presence of religion leads us to another reflection:",
         "source": [
            {
               "type": 1,
               "uuid": "75b904ee-b115-4264-9708-0bbd67c7b8b2",
               "text": "Britannica Editors",
               "page": "Sui Dynasty",
               "date_time": {
                  "type": "gregory",
                  "year": "2025",
                  "month": "3",
                  "day": "3"
               }
            },
            {
               "type": 1,
               "uuid": "cd42262b-9421-4c44-b273-25caea45bfa8",
               "text": "Cartwright, M.",
               "page": "Sui Dynasty",
               "date_time": {
                  "type": "gregory",
                  "year": "2017",
                  "month": "9",
                  "day": "22"
               }
            },
            {
               "type": 1,
               "uuid": "eecbdaad-5b22-4aca-89f2-37c4f1dded01",
               "text": "Copp, P.",
               "page": "pp. 75",
               "date_time": {
                  "type": "gregory",
                  "year": "",
                  "month": "",
                  "day": ""
               }
            },
            {
               "type": 1,
               "uuid": "eecbdaad-5b22-4aca-89f2-37c4f1dded01",
               "text": "Copp, P.",
               "page": "pp. 80, 82 - 85",
               "date_time": {
                  "type": "gregory",
                  "year": "",
                  "month": "",
                  "day": ""
               }
            },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "cff9edbf-cd50-44cd-8ef7-54197d68c82b",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Chronology",
